Hygiene and Protection: They provide with sanitizer, and mask. No other PPEs were provided. Seats were clean and air circulation aircraft seemed normal. 2. Timings: Aircraft took off and landed normally as per the scheduled arrival/departure times. 3. Food: Ordered vegetarian and it seemed fine. I think the quantity was a bit less \uD83D\uDE1B. It was nicely packaged and served warm (where applicable) 4. Courtesy of Staff: Staff movement in the cabin was way lesser than normal. But when summoned, they seemed to approach just okay. 5. Entertainment: Systems are up and running. No issues whatsoever. The Hyderabad bound flight had newer equipment I suppose. 6. Luggage: Close to 5 passengers (including me) lost (mishandled by airport ground staff) their baggage in DOHA. Very disappointing. Hyderabad airport had grievance counter very near to the carousel. Submitted the complaint and hope to get a call in 24 hours. (Update: Got back my luggage within 48 hours; delivered at doorstep) Immigration at Doha: None. Had a layover of 1.5 hours and it was smooth. Had enough time to catch the connection. Immigration at Hyderabad: 1. Went smooth and seamless. 2. Was asked for the above mentioned documents at 3 different counters. 3. Customs went smooth too. Have a safe flight. At SFO we had to present negative RTPCR, completed air suvidha and UK passenger locator forms to check-in. Yes, you need the UK passenger locator form even if you are just transiting. Please encourage deserving students to apply and *forward this email to your friends.* https://www.usgfoundation.org/scholarships_and_reports/scholarship_applications Scholarship Applications The Georgia Association of Physicians of Indian Heritage Scholarship Fund Purpose The Georgia Association of Physicians of Indian Heritage Scholarship is an annual scholarship for the support of a need-based scholarship to one or more students to assist the student(s) with the cost of attending a University System of Georgia institution. Eligibility Criteria The student must be full-time enrolled at a University of Georgia System institution at the time of award of the scholarship. Preference will be given to a student pursuing an undergraduate degree. The student will have documented indication of financial need. The student will carry an overall 2.75 or above grade point average at the time of applying for the scholarship. Preference will be given to students who exhibit a connection with India or have traveled to India during their lifetime. The selected students agree to attend the GAPI annual spring meeting to be recognized. Student expenses associated with travel to the annual meeting are the responsibility of the student, however, students are encouraged to work with their respective institutional scholarship office to determine if funds are available to assist with travel. Selection Five scholarships in the amount of $1,500 each will be awarded annually unless another amount is specified. The student(s) will be selected based on an application process by an independent selection committee of no less than 3 persons who do not have a personal relationship with the candidates, and will be appointed by the Vice Chancellor for Development of the University System of Georgia Foundation. The selected student(s) will be notified no later than December 31 of the same year as the application is submitted. The student will be asked to confirm attendance at the student’s selected institution. The application period for this academic year is now open and will close on December 31.
